t\u0027s just random chaos.\n*   If it\u0027s unbreakable Fate, why fight it? Makes no sense.\n*   If it\u0027s Providence that listens, then make yourself *worthy* of getting help.\n*   If it\u0027s just random chaos, sweet! Be glad you\u0027ve got a brain inside you to navigate the mess. If the chaos sweeps you away physically, let it take the meat suit and the energy; it *can\u0027t* take your mind.\nThink about it: A lamp shines bright until someone puts it out. Are you gonna let your truth, justice, and self-control get snuffed out before your time is up? Hell no.\n\n**16. Dealing with Assholes.**\n*Original:* See someone do wrong: How know it was wrong? If was, how know he wasn\u0027t condemning self (like tearing face)? Wanting evil man not to do wrong like wanting fig tree not produce juice, infants not cry, horse not neigh. What else can he do? If man enough, cure this disposition (in yourself).\n*Bro Version:* Someone seems to screw up? First, how do you *know* it was wrong from their angle? Second, even if it *was* wrong, how do you know they aren\u0027t already beating themselves up over it, like metaphorically clawing their own face? Trying to force a bad person *not* to act badly is like demanding a fig tree not have fig juice, babies not cry, or horses not neigh. It\u0027s their nature, given their current screwed-up state! What else *can* they do with that mindset? So, if you\u0027re tough enough, focus on fixing *your own* tendency to get bent out of shape about it.\n\n**17-18. Right Action, Clear Sight.**\n*Original:* If not right, don\u0027t do. If not true, don\u0027t say. Impulse to see always what creates impression, open it up: cause, matter, relation, time limit.\n*Bro Version:* Simple rules: If it ain\u0027t right, don\u0027t do it. If it ain\u0027t true, don\u0027t say it. Your default move should be: Whatever thought or impression pops up, really *look* at it. Take it apart: What caused it? What\u0027s it made of? How does it relate to stu